        "1650ee8d": {
          "questionId": "1650ee8d",
          "textAnswers": {
            "answers": [
              {
                "value": "I think the assessment highlights a format mismatch between the benchmark data and the use case output format (e.g. reporting structure from UN OCHA documents), which is a problem other use cases would have. This issue is hard to address unless a specific benchmark for the use case is developed. I would focus more on the content and less on stylistic genre-convention: \"(numbered bullets, standardized headers, parroquia-level\ndamnificado figures)\". In other words, if the content is there in the output summary, a follow up stage could focus on reformatting the output. \nAs a minor comment, I believe the term \"parroquia-level damnificado\" is an hallucinations or super specific example that I would not expect in this type of document"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
